    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Passages or aisles in Greek theaters concentric with the outer wall. For similar features in Roman theaters, use "praecinctiones."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000077471/Sturgis, Dictionary of Architecture and Building (1901)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Doorgangen tussen de hoger en lager gelegen rijen zitplaatsen in Griekse theaters. Gebruik 'praecinctiones' voor gelijksoortige doorgangen in Romeinse theaters.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052396/Koch, Europese bouwstijlen (1988)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Konzentrisch mit der Außenmauer verlaufender Durchgang oder Gang in antiken griechischen Theatern. Ähnliche Gänge in römischen Theatern werden "Praecinctiones" genannt.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
